<Sect2 Id="DCEADG.GDSXOC.div.25">
<Title>Object Types</Title>
<Para><IndexTerm Id="DCEADG.GDSXOC.indx.80">
<Primary>object</Primary>
<Secondary>type</Secondary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm Id="DCEADG.GDSXOC.indx.81">
<Primary>attribute</Primary>
<Secondary>OM syntax</Secondary>
<Tertiary>object type</Tertiary>
</IndexTerm>An OM attribute with syntax template Object(<Literal>*</Literal>) has
<Literal>OM_S_OBJECT</Literal> as syntax and a subobject as a value.  For example,
one of the OM attributes of the OM class <Literal>DS_C_DS_DN</Literal> is
<Literal>DS_RDNS</Literal>.  <Literal>DS_RDNS</Literal> is listed in the OM attribute table for
<Literal>DS_C_DS_DN</Literal> as having a value syntax of Object(<Literal>DS_C_DS_RDN</Literal>),
as shown in Table 5-5.
</Para>
